Main Research interest

The main focus of my research is the study of soil respiration within a deciduous and coniferous forest stand through long – term automatic chambers. Then I compare and contrast different models such as the Q10 model and neural networks to fit the data in order to obtain missing carbon fluxes from periods with no measurement data.
